Package: interdep
Title: Prepare Dyadic Data for Multilevel Models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Pascal", "Küng", , "kueng.pascal@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Helps researchers prepare cross-sectional and intensive
    longitudinal dyadic data for multilevel models, including generalized
    multilevel models. The package supports common dyadic designs with one kind
    of dyad, while also handling studies that combine different kinds of dyads,
    such as female-male, female-female, and male-male couples. It validates
    long-format dyadic data and creates the role, composition, temporal
    predictor decomposition, and model-ready columns needed for dyadic
    multilevel model parameterizations such as APIM, DIM, and DSM.
    Prepared data can be used with multilevel model engines such as 'glmmTMB'.
